01:32:57,892 --> 01:33:01,592
That's one of the first things
I noticed about you.

692
01:33:02,491 --> 01:33:04,558
You like to cruise.

693
01:33:06,810 --> 01:33:10,077
- Suzie . . .
- Take college, for instance.

694
01:33:10,889 --> 01:33:15,122
I bet you only took classes
if the finals were multiple choice.

695
01:33:16,129 --> 01:33:19,095
You bought no books.
You'd borrow a girl's -

696
01:33:19,850 --> 01:33:22,616
- and then you'd have to fuck her.

697
01:33:23,330 --> 01:33:26,130
Is that how it went?

698
01:33:27,848 --> 01:33:30,648
Yeah.

699
01:33:31,369 --> 01:33:35,402
Well, I've got a good pop quiz
for you. Multiple choice, of course.

700
01:33:37,608 --> 01:33:43,274
Before sailing away, Medea killed
King Creon and the princess with . .?

701
01:33:45,288 --> 01:33:47,221
A rock?

702
01:33:47,768 --> 01:33:50,768
A spear gun? Or . . .

703
01:33:51,528 --> 01:33:55,028
- A little poison?
- Poison !

704
01:33:59,328 --> 01:34:01,428
Good guess!

705
01:34:31,405 --> 01:34:34,038
Nice truck.

706
01:34:40,844 --> 01:34:43,910
Selling your boat?

707
01:34:47,524 --> 01:34:52,258
This was Suzie's boat.
Guess she won't be needing it now.

708
01:34:54,363 --> 01:34:58,530
Funny, I wouldn't have guessed
Suzie was a sailor.

709
01:35:00,643 --> 01:35:06,543
The old lady had her tested once.
Her IQ was way up, around 200.

710
01:35:08,684 --> 01:35:12,350
That girl could do anything
she put her mind to.

711
01:36:19,398 --> 01:36:23,531
You know, when I got busted
I called you about 100 times.

712
01:36:28,998 --> 01:36:33,531
I really believed that stuff
about you being my friend.

713
01:36:34,598 --> 01:36:37,531
Was I naive!

714
01:36:40,359 --> 01:36:42,359
What came out better?

715
01:36:42,917 --> 01:36:46,917
That straw up Kelly's nose,
or that dog collar around your neck?

716
01:36:47,877 --> 01:36:50,811
What do you think, Mr. Lombardo?

717
01:37:05,116 --> 01:37:09,549
He seems to like the same places
you do. Funny you never met.

718
01:37:10,595 --> 01:37:15,661
Real funny. You're wrong about this,
and I could get busted right here.

719
01:37:16,836 --> 01:37:21,436
Trust me, the guy's dirty, he'll
love it. Especially killing me.

720
01:37:22,514 --> 01:37:25,014
Get out of here,
make a new friend.

721
01:37:37,553 --> 01:37:40,120
What are you drinking?

722
01:37:51,754 --> 01:37:55,887
Got the pressure too tight.
You'll crush the fucking evidence.

723
01:38:00,153 --> 01:38:03,219
For Christ's sake.

724
01:38:16,872 --> 01:38:20,072
- Hello, Kelly.
- What are you doing here?

725
01:39:04,589 --> 01:39:07,822
May I ask you a question,
Miss Toller?

726
01:39:08,629 --> 01:39:12,529
Did you enjoy being
a guest of the state?

727
01:39:13,948 --> 01:39:17,148
Boy, I hope I never make you mad.

728
01:39:20,028 --> 01:39:22,562
The cash is just
walking-around money.

729
01:39:23,228 --> 01:39:27,195
The cheque is the account, minus
a million for Ruby and Walter -

730
01:39:28,147 --> 01:39:30,580
- plus my usual fee.

731
01:39:31,227 --> 01:39:34,060
Case closed.

732
01:39:44,747 --> 01:39:47,381
Suzie . . .

733
01:39:48,867 --> 01:39:51,767
Be good.

